tasks.description:
Extend `src/config.ts` with a `CamoufoxConfig` interface covering all 19 camoufox-js launch options. Add `camoufox?: CamoufoxConfig` to `BrowseConfig`. Also add a `loadCamoufoxConfig(localDir?: string)` function that: (1) reads browse.json camoufox section via `loadConfig()`, (2) checks `BROWSE_CAMOUFOX_PROFILE` env var, (3) if set, loads `.browse/profiles/<name>.json` and merges (profile wins), (4) returns the merged `CamoufoxConfig`. This function is called by the resolver at startup — no changes to `getRuntime()` signature needed.

The interface maps 1:1 to camoufox-js LaunchOptions:
```typescript
export interface CamoufoxConfig {
  os?: string | string[];           // 'windows' | 'macos' | 'linux' or array
  blockImages?: boolean;
  blockWebrtc?: boolean;
  blockWebgl?: boolean;
  disableCoop?: boolean;
  geoip?: string | boolean;         // true = auto-detect from proxy IP, or specific IP
  humanize?: boolean | number;      // true or max duration in seconds
  locale?: string | string[];
  addons?: string[];                // Firefox addon paths
  fonts?: string[];                 // Font family names
  customFontsOnly?: boolean;
  screen?: { minWidth?: number; maxWidth?: number; minHeight?: number; maxHeight?: number };
  window?: [number, number];        // Fixed [width, height]
  fingerprint?: Record<string, unknown>;  // BrowserForge fingerprint
  ffVersion?: number;
  headless?: boolean | 'virtual';
  mainWorldEval?: boolean;
  firefoxUserPrefs?: Record<string, unknown>;
  proxy?: string | { server: string; username?: string; password?: string };
  enableCache?: boolean;
  debug?: boolean;
}
```

Update `src/engine/resolver.ts` camoufox loader (line 171-182) to:
1. Import `loadConfig` from `../config`
2. Read `config.camoufox` section
3. Map BrowseConfig camelCase keys to camoufox-js snake_case keys
4. Merge with defaults (humanize: true, enable_cache: true, headless: from BROWSE_HEADED)
5. Pass the full options object to `camou.launchOptions()`

The key mapping:
- `blockImages` → `block_images`
- `blockWebrtc` → `block_webrtc`
- `blockWebgl` → `block_webgl`
- `disableCoop` → `disable_coop`
- `mainWorldEval` → `main_world_eval`
- `customFontsOnly` → `custom_fonts_only`
- `ffVersion` → `ff_version`
- `enableCache` → `enable_cache`
- `firefoxUserPrefs` → `firefox_user_prefs`
- Rest pass through as-is (os, geoip, humanize, locale, addons, fonts, screen, window, fingerprint, proxy, debug)
